{
  "texts": [
    "By identifying different patients, the system can provide personalized and targeted rehabilitation training to each patient based on their specific needs.",
    "This approach is more effective than a one-size-fits-all approach as it takes into account individual differences in gait and movement patterns.",
    "The system has been validated on 3 healthy subjects with an accuracy of 0.95.",
    "Overall, the paper demonstrates the potential of combining technology, such as the Kinect sensor along with exoskeletons to improve the effectiveness of rehabilitation training and provide personalized care to patients.",
    "The paper Lin et al. (2017) proposes a real-time electromyography-triggered controller for a pneumatic artificial muscle-actuated lower-limb exoskeleton."
  ]
}